<h1>Hello, World</h1>
<p><span class="fn n p-name" itemprop="name"><span class="given-name p-given-name" itemprop="givenName">Colin</span> <abbr class="additional-name p-additional-name" itemprop="additionalName">M.</span> <span class="family-name p-family-name" itemprop="familyName">Ford</span></span> is a <span itemprop="address" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/PostalAddress"><span class="locality p-locality" itemprop="addressLocality">{{ site.locality }}</span></span>-based <span itemprop="jobTitle">{{ site.jobTitle }}</span>. He currently works at <span itemprop="worksFor" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization"><a href="https://monotype.com" class="p-org org h-card" itemprop="name">Monotype</a></span>, and for 10 years before that worked at <span itemprop="worksFor" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Organization"><a href="https://typography.com" class="p-org org h-card" itemprop="name">Hoefler &amp; Co.</a></span>. He has more than a decade and a half of experience in <span itemprop="knowsAbout">typeface design and engineering</span>.</p>

<p>He is a graduate of the <span itemprop="alumniOf" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/EducationalOrganization">Type and Media masters program at the <span itemprop="name">Koninklijke Academie van Beeldende Kunsten</span> (KABK) in <span itemprop="location">The Hague</span></span>, and of the <span itemprop="alumniOf" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/EducationalOrganization"><span itemprop="name">Maryland Institute College of Art</span> (MICA) in <span itemprop="location">Baltimore</span></span>. Since he joined H&Co in 2011, he has worked on a variety of projects, including the design of Decimal, which was featured in the Netflix documentary series Abstract, and used by U.S. President Joe Biden.</p> 

<p>Since 2020, Colin teaches a course in font production for the Type@Cooper program at The Cooper Union for the Advancement of Science and Art in NYC. The course covers OpenType file structure, vertical metrics, font naming, encodings, GSUB/GPOS features, interpolation, kerning, hinting, variable fonts, and color fonts. He has also lectured and taught workshops on Emoji at the Atelier National de Recherche Typographique, The Letterform Archive, The Cooper Union, and MICA.</p>